{"word":"θαλαμηπόλος","slug":"θαλαμηπόλος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>θαλαμηπόλος</b></el> <el>(θᾰλᾰμη-πόλος, ἡ,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><el>πολέομαι</el>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>a chamber-maid, waiting maid</i>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>a eunuch of the bed chamber</i>, <b><a href='S:Plutarch'>Plut.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>rarely, <i>a bridegroom</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>as <a href='S:Adjective'>adj.</a> <i>bridal</i>, <b><a href='S:Anthology'>Anth.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}